:name: PMW3610 wireless split (peripheral w/ simulated PMW3610 + central + host)
:description: Three nRF52840s on one BLE medium: split PERIPHERAL (real PMW3610 on
:description: SPIM0) -> split CENTRAL (Studio + PMW3610 relay bridge) -> renode-ble-host.

# Module-local counterpart of zmk-west-commands' three_machine_ble.resc, adapted
# so the split PERIPHERAL machine carries a *simulated PMW3610* on SPIM0 (via the
# compiled-in PMW3610.cs sensor model + the LATCH-aware GPIO), so the peripheral's
# ZMK PMW3610 driver inits for real and answers relayed GetInfo/ReadRegister
# requests. The host drives the PMW3610 custom Studio RPC against the CENTRAL,
# which relays to the peripheral over the split event relay.
#
# All path variables are materialized (absolute) by pmw3610_ble_split_lib.py:
#   $*_platform : per-machine real repls (FICR-injected). $peripheral_platform is
#     the sensor variant xiao_nrf52840_real_pmw3610.repl. $ccm : fake AES-CCM.
#   $cs_pmw / $cs_latch : the C# sensor + LATCH-GPIO models (compiled first).

using sysbus

$central_bin?=@central.elf
$peripheral_bin?=@peripheral.elf
$host_bin?=@host.elf
$central_platform?=@platforms/xiao_nrf52840_real.repl
$peripheral_platform?=@platforms/xiao_nrf52840_real_pmw3610.repl
$host_platform?=@platforms/xiao_nrf52840_real.repl
$ccm?=@platforms/ccm.repl
$c_console?=3471
$c_rpc?=3472
$p_console?=3473
$h_console?=3474

# Compile the C# sensor + LATCH-GPIO models before any platform that instantiates
# them loads (the peripheral platform references SPI.PMW3610 + NRF52840_GPIO_WithLatch).
include $cs_pmw
include $cs_latch

emulation CreateBLEMedium "wireless"
emulation SetGlobalQuantum "0.00001"

# ---- central (Studio + PMW3610 split-relay bridge, GAP central + peripheral) --
mach create "central"
machine LoadPlatformDescription $central_platform
machine LoadPlatformDescription $ccm
connector Connect sysbus.radio wireless
emulation CreateServerSocketTerminal $c_console "central_console" false
connector Connect sysbus.uart0 central_console
emulation CreateServerSocketTerminal $c_rpc "central_rpc" false
connector Connect sysbus.uart1 central_rpc
sysbus LoadELF $central_bin

# ---- peripheral (real PMW3610 on SPIM0) --------------------------------------
mach create "peripheral"
machine LoadPlatformDescription $peripheral_platform
machine LoadPlatformDescription $ccm
connector Connect sysbus.radio wireless
emulation CreateServerSocketTerminal $p_console "peripheral_console" false
connector Connect sysbus.uart0 peripheral_console
sysbus LoadELF $peripheral_bin

# ---- host (renode-ble-host) --------------------------------------------------
mach create "host"
machine LoadPlatformDescription $host_platform
machine LoadPlatformDescription $ccm
connector Connect sysbus.radio wireless
emulation CreateServerSocketTerminal $h_console "host_console" false
connector Connect sysbus.uart0 host_console
sysbus LoadELF $host_bin

# The lib sets up SEGGER RTT capture on the peripheral, preloads both ZMK halves'
# NVS (erased 0xFF), and issues `start` after connecting sockets.
